From Alex Milshteyn Subject Re Is MSG sensitivity superstition In article writes I wouldn't call it a double blind but one local restaurant's soup provokes an impressive migraine headache for my wife that one take out and no Nothing Quote Chinese Restaurant Syndrome CRS a transient syndrome associated with arterial dilatation due to ingestion of monosodium glutamate which is used liberally in seasoning chinese food it is characterized by throbbing of the head lightheadedness tightness of the jaw neck and shoulders and End Source Dorland's Illustrated Medical Dictionary edition Saunders p This was known long Brain produces and uses some MSG naturally but not in doses it is served at some chinese Having said that i might add that in MHO MSG does not enhance flavor enoughf for me to miss When I go to chinese places I order food without Goos places will do it for A prerequisite for such a service would be a waiter capable of understanding what you Good am Alexander Milshteyn CIPR MGH in Boston Vox Fax